The Apache Software Foundation and the Apache HTTP Server Project are
pleased to announce the release of version 2.0.54 of the Apache HTTP
Server ("Apache").

This version of Apache is principally a bug and security fix release.
The following security vulnerabilities are addressed in this release:

CAN-2005-0490: mod_auth_digest: Fixed a potential buffer overflow when
               parsing Authorization headers.

CAN-2005-0989: mod_ssl: Fixed a potential memory disclosure if a request
               uses the SSL hostname extension.

We consider this release to be the best version of Apache 2.0 available
and encourage users of all prior versions to upgrade.

Apache 2.0.54 is available for download from:
  http://httpd.apache.org/download.cgi

Please see the CHANGES_2.0 file, included in the distribution, for a
full list of changes.

The Apache HTTP Server Project
